      "description": "Generic one-loop pentagon normalised to unit leading singularity in $D = 6 - 2\\varepsilon$ dimensions with arbitrary internal and external mass configuration. The paper uses the diagrammatic coaction to derive the total differential of the pentagon entirely from its cuts: contributions come from triple cuts (labelled by triples $(ijk)$) weighted by triangle-like coefficients, quadruple cuts (labelled by $(ijkl)$) weighted by box-like coefficients, and the maximal five-fold cut at order $\\varepsilon^1$ multiplied by the pentagon itself. The result bypasses IBP reduction and yields the canonical-form differential equation for any one-loop integral.",
